    • Constructor Detail

      • NetworkEntity

        @Raw
public NetworkEntity​(java.lang.Integer xPos,
                     java.lang.Integer yPos,
                     EnvironmentMap environment,
                     java.lang.Integer transmissionPower,
                     java.lang.Integer SF,
                     java.lang.Integer transmissionPowerThreshold)
        A constructor generating a Network with a given x-position, y-position, environment and transmission power.
        Parameters:
        xPos - The x-coordinate of the entity on the map.
        yPos - The y-coordinate of the entity on the map.
        environment - The map of the environment.
        transmissionPower - The transmission power of the entity.
        SF - The spreading factor of the entity.
        transmissionPowerThreshold - The threshold for discriminating different transmissions.
        Post:
        If the x-coordinate was valid, it is set., If the x-coordinate was not valid, it is set to 0., If the y-coordinate was valid, it is set., If the y-coordinate was not valid, it is set to 0., If the transmission power was valid, it is set., If the transmission power was not valid, it is set to 0.
